@node intro "Introduction.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Intro
  ~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   This is a MUI-program that makes it very easy to view the daily
   e-mails that can be ordered from the TV-guide site www.dagenstv.com.

   If you have seen TView you know what I mean. But DagensTV has more
   features, like savable and temporary reminds, it can be automaticly
   updated every day if you have your computer on all the time like I
   do.

   Included is also rexx-scripts for YAM that automates the transfer
   of the e-mail contents to the program.


@endnode

@node install "Installation.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Installation
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   Just copy the program or preferably the drawer with the icon and
   this guide to somewhere on your hard disk.

   If you are using YAM you probably also want to add the
   MoveDagensTV.rexx script to YAM and add it to the script menu for
   easy access.
   NOTE: You need to create a new folder in YAM called DagensTV where
         all e-mails will be archived or you have to modify the
         scripts to either delete the mails or move them somewhere
         else.

   If you use my reminder program DRemind you should set up a remind
   to execute the ExtractDagensTV.rexx script at a daily basis. If you
   have the computer on all the time or atleast when the e-mails arrive
   (usually between 06.00 and 08.00) you can set up a remind to execute
   this script at this time, then DagensTV will automatically be
   updated whether it's running or not, every day.
   Otherwise you can set up a remind "Once at Startup" (providing YAM
   is started before DRemind) which executes the script and updates
   the TV-Guie first time you start your computer every day.

   Of course you can also manually save the text from the daily e-mails
   in a text file to load as a TV-Guide to DagensTV.


@endnode

@node req "Requirements.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Requirements
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   OS version 37+

   MUI v3+
   NList.mcc

   Asl.library v37+

   It is also recommended to use YAM as a mailer so you can use the
   arexx-scripts without modification.

   RexxMast must ofcourse also be running if you want to use the
   scripts.


@endnode

@node usage "Usage.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Usage
  ~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

  Start the program, it has a MUI-GUI.

  The main window has a list of all programs. This can be configured
  from the menu/Preferences/DagensTV Settings..

  You can click on the time to see all programs that start this
  particular time. If you click on a program you will see some info
  about it.

  If you double-click on a program you will set a temporary remind
  on it and the program will be in @{b}bold@{ub} font. This means
  that DagensTV will popup a remind about a minute before the program
  starts. Double-click again to remove the temporary remind.

  @{u}Now over to the preference window:@{uu}

  @{i}Preferences @{ui}

    @{b}Scroll the list with time@{ub}
      Set this if you want the list to scroll to make the current
      program(s) to always be visible in the list.
  
    @{b}Activate the current program@{ub}
      This works best together with @{b}Scroll the list with time@{ub}. It
      makes the program that was most recently started to be the active
      on in the list.
  
    @{b}View in one column@{ub}
      If you have many channels or not so many program totally you
      probably want to use this feature. (This is one feature that I
      missed in TView along with the possibility of showing all program
      the whole day in the same column.)

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}Don't ask when double-clicking for remind@{ub}
      Usually you will get a confirmation requester asking you if you
      really want to set or remove a temporary remind but with this
      set you will not get that requester.
  
    @{b}Don't remind if the TV-guide is old@{ub}
      If you have some permanent reminds set you many or may not want
      DagensTV to use those reminds when the TV-Guide is old. If you
      only have TV-series that is on on a daily basis it usually doesn't
      matter if the guide is one day old, but sometimes it's annoying to
      be reminded about programs that is not on this day, beacuse the
      guide is old. It's up to you :)
  
    @{b}DisplayBeep when reminding@{ub}
      Set this if you want to hear (or see) the system "boing" sound and
      possibly a screen flash when a remind pops up.

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}Re-iconify when acknowledging a remind@{ub}
      If this is set and a remind pops up and you press "Ok" DagensTV
      will iconify itself again. There will also be a new button in the
      remind window so that you can override the re-iconification if you
      want.
  
    @{b}Start iconified@{ub}
      Set this if you don't want the window to open on startup.
  
    @{b}Close button iconifies@{ub}
      Use this if you want to make the window close button to iconify
      DagensTV instead of quitting it. You can still quit from the
      menu though.
  
    @{b}Load DagensTV Guide on startup@{ub}
      Set this if you don't want to load the TV-Guide manually every
      time you start DagensTV.
  
    @{b}Remind timeout@{ub}
      Set the checkmark and specify a timeout (in minutes) with the
      slider if you want popped up remind to automatically disappear
      after a certain time. If you're not home, or doing something else
      for a few hour it's usually no point in a popped up remind to
      stay open any longer as the program most likely has ended a long
      time ago anyway.
  
    @{b}Default path to TV guide@{ub}
      This is the path (including filename) where DagensTV will look
      for the textfile containing the body of the daily e-mail when
      using the arexx command RELOAD or when you pick "Reload the TV
      Guide" from the Project menu.
      Make sure this is the same path as in the arexx scripts. Default
      is "SYS:T/DagensTV".
  
    @{b}Delete DagensTV file..@{ub}
      @{b}Never@{ub}         - The text file mentioned above will never be
                      deleted.
      @{b}After load@{ub}    - The text file will be deleted after you have
                      loaded the file into DagensTV.
      @{b}When quitting@{ub} - The text file will be deleted when you quit
                      DagensTV if you have loaded the file.

  @{i}Auto reminds @{ui}

    This is where you can manage all reminds that are automatically
    applied to every matching program everytime a TV-Guide is loaded.
    Also temporary reminds end up here.

    You can double-click on a temporary remind in this list to make
    it a permanent remind that will be saved when you save prefs.

    The list of reminds has a few columns:

    @{i}@{b}State @{ub}@{ui}
      Off  - If @{b}Disable all reminds@{ub} has been selected.
      N/M  - No Match. Means that no program in the list match this
             remind.
      Ok   - Means that a program has a remind on it, and this
             remind is the one that matched.
      Temp - This is a temporary remind that will be forgotten
             when you quit DagensTV. To set or remove a temporary
             remind you just double-click on a program.

    @{i}@{b}Num @{ub}@{ui}
      The number of programs in the list that this remind matched.

    @{i}@{b}Search @{ub}@{ui}
      This is where in a TV-program to search for the given pattern.
      Program - Search in the name of the program.
      Info    - Search in the information text of the program.
      Channel - Match the name or part of in the channel.
      All     - This will search in all fields related to a
                program including time.

    @{i}@{b}Match @{ub}@{ui}
      How to match the pattern to the search field.
      If Exists - This will succeed if the pattern exists as a
                  string somewhere in the search field.
      Exactly   - Now the search field must be exactly the same
                  as the pattern to succeed.

    @{i}@{b}String to search for @{ub}@{ui}
      This is the string, or pattern, to search for.

    @{i}@{b}Command to execute @{ub}@{ui}
      Here is the command line you want to execute when this
      remind pops up.


    @{b}Search in@{ub}
      This is where in a TV-program to search for the given pattern.
      Program name - Search in, or match, the name of the program.
      Info text    - Search in the information text of the program.
      Channel name - Match the name or part of in the channel.
      All fields   - This will search in all fields related to a
                     program, including time.

    @{b}Match@{ub}
      How to match the pattern to the search field.
      If Exists - This will succeed if the pattern exists as a
                  string somewhere in the search field.
      Exactly   - Now the search field must be exactly the same
                  as the pattern to succeed.

    @{b}Pattern@{ub}
      This is the string that should match, or exist in the
      search field you have specified. Note that it is really
      not a pattern, you cannot use #? or * or something (yet).

    @{b}Command@{ub}
      Here you can specify a DOS command line to execute when
      the remind pops upp.

    @{b}Add@{ub}
      Create a new permanent remind.
      After you have pressed add you can fill in the fields.

    @{b}Remove@{ub}
      This will remove the selected remind from the list. You
      need to press save to make the changes permanent.

    @{b}Clear@{ub}
      This will remove all reminds from the list. You need to
      press save to make the changes permanent.


  @{b}Save@{ub}
    This will save the preferences including reminds that are not
    temporary reminds. It will ask you to convert any temporary
    reminds to permanent reminds.

  @{b}Use@{ub}
    This will make your preferences remembered until you restart
    your computer, excluding reminds. Any reminds not saved will
    be forgotten if you quit DagensTV.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
    Exit DagensTV. The DagensTV text file will be deleted now if
    that is what you have specified.

  @{b}Cancel@{ub}
    Revert to your previous preferences. All remind will be
    flushed and the last saved reminds will be reloaded.


  @{u}The Project menu@{uu}

    @{b}Load a DagensTV guide..@{ub}
      This will let you pick out a text file by hand, using an ASL-
      requester, that will be loaded as a TV-guide.

    @{b}Reload the TV-guide@{ub}
      This will flush the current list of programs and load the
      text file from the default TV-guide path.

    @{b}Clear list@{ub}
      This will clear the list of TV-prograns.

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}About@{ub}
      Show some info about the program.

    @{b}OnyxSoft@{ub}
      Show some info about OnyxSoft.

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}Iconify@{ub}
      Iconify DagensTV the way you have specified in MUI.

    @{b}Quit@{ub}
      Exit DagensTV. The DagensTV text file will be deleted now
      if that is what you have specified.

  @{u}The Preferences menu@{uu}

    @{b}DagensTV settings..@{ub}
      This will open the preference window where you can change
      the behavior of DagensTV. This is also the place where you
      can add/edit/remove the reminds.

    @{b}Last saved settings@{ub}
      If you have pressed Use you can use this to reload the
      last saved settings including the list of reminds.

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}MUI settings...@{ub}
      This will open the standard MUI settings for DagensTV.

    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}Scroll the list with time@{ub}
      Set this if you want the list to scroll to make the current
      program(s) to always be visible in the list.
      (Same as in the prefs.)

    @{b}Single/Multi column list@{ub}
      This is a quicker way to switch between a single or multi
      column list for the TV-programs.

    @{b}Disable all reminds@{ub}
      this will temporarily prevent any remind from popping up.
      This is practical if you are going to play a game or watch
      a movie (on the computer) and don't want to be interrupted.

      In OS4 this feature will be automatic.


@endnode

@node news "News.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}News and Changes
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

  @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Added support for the new HTML e-mails.

 @{b}v1.41
 ~~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Found a bad hit which occurs when reloading the TV-guide.
    (It sure is easy to find bugs when the OS has memory protection,
    although it's very limited.. (OS4) :-))

 @{b}v1.4
 ~~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If DagensTV was iconified with the prefs window open and a
    remind popped up the remind would contain garbage (because
    of an unexpected double-use of a string variable in this
    particular event).
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} DagensTV crashed on OS4 because of a too small stack generated
    by the E-compiler. It has now been raise to fix the problem.
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added Spacebar as shortkey to close the remind window without
    iconifying DagensTV, if it is set to this in the prefs.

 @{b}v1.3
 ~~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it's possible to prevent reminds from popping up when the
    TV-Guide is old.
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a feature to make DagensTV re-iconify itself when you press
    Ok in a remind requester if DagensTV was iconified when the remind
    can up.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a remind timeout value which you can set to something between
    1 and 300 minutes and that automatically will remove a remind after
    this time. This is optional ofcourse.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Finally managed to create this guide!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now DagensTV iconifies with it's own icon, not the MUI default icon
    as before!
  
 @{b}v1.21
 ~~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug with the balance object being saved wrong.
  
 @{b}v1.2@{ub}  (v1.21 is just a quick fix for the big release v1.2)
 @{b}~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now there is a list where you can specify programs to be reminded
    about! If you double-click on a program to set an alarm on it
    this will also show up in this list. You can add keywords to
    match exactly or "if exists" for the program name, program info,
    channel or all.
    This list is saved and will be scanned agains the programs
    everytime a new TV-Guide arrives and automatically set alarms
    on the programs you have specified!
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Cleaned up the menu and added hotkeys to some menu items.
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the relative sizes between the lister and the text info field
    adjustable with the balance object is also saved when you save
    the prefs!
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changed the list to use NList(view) so that you can scroll sideways!
  
 @{b}v1.11
 ~~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a complementary menu option "Scroll list with time" so that
    you can easily switch the feature on or off. Most useful to switch
    off when you are reading the info text to prevent the list from
    skipping away.
  
 @{b}v1.1
 ~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can have the most current program to always be activated in
    the list! This is an additional feature to the already existing
    "Scroll the list with time" feature.
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can put alarms on a program by double-clicking on it!
  
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The default path in DagensTV and the rexx scripts were not coherent.
  
 @{b}v1.0
 ~~~~@{ub}
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Initial release.


@endnode

